[Vaccinations to prevent EEE are available for horses. These are very effective when administered correctly. Initially a horse needs a set of 2 vaccines about 3 weeks apart, and then annually thereafter. However, immunity to EEE in a horse wanes fast, and it is recommended, in areas where there is EEE, to revaccinate horses about every 4 months. The vaccine is considerably cheaper than losing an animal to death or paying for an extended animal hospital stay. Most horse owners have a substantial investment in their animals, so please take care of the investment and the animals and vaccinate them. There are also mosquito and fly sprays specifically for horses. Please use these too.

Also protect yourself with appropriate sprays and limit your time out of doors to when the mosquitoes are less active, which is the main part of the day. Mosquitoes are most active at dusk and dawn. Use appropriate mosquito repellent spray on yourselves. - Mod.TG

